@node main fidonet.lib
@{b}What the heck is this?@{ub}

This thing is all about fidonet.lib, a linker library that provides you
with easy means for writing Fidonet message packets (Type 2, FSC-0039).
This is the first version, and only has functions for writing packets.

@{b}How do I use it?@{ub}

Call MakePkt(). Then call MakeMsg(), write the message body (to, from,
subject and text) into the packet file, and repeat this as many times
as you want, once for each message. Then, call ClosePkt() to finish
the packet.

@{b}What?@{ub}

Take a look at the example source code fidonet.c that accompanies
the library. It should be everything you need to understand the use.

